function foo() {
    // code
};

```

Examples of **correct** code for this rule:

```js
/*eslint no-extra-semi: "error"*/

var x = 5;

var foo = function() {
    // code
};

```

## When Not To Use It

If you intentionally use extra semicolons then you can disable this rule.

